# 👾 Axiom MLOps: VodaPay Instant EFT Engine

![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)
![Python 3.13+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.13+-blue.svg)
![W&B Tracking](https://img.shields.io/badge/W&B-Active-orange)
![Prefect Cloud](https://img.shields.io/badge/Prefect-Orchestration-blueviolet)

A production-ready machine learning pipeline designed to predict **Instant EFT Success** for VodaPay Virtual Card funding. This project transitions with built-in auditability and governance.

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```text
.
├── src/axiom_mlops_project/
│   ├── api.py            # FastAPI Production Service (Real-time Inference)
│   ├── lineage.py        # Data Provenance & MD5 Audit Trails
│   ├── explanations.py   # SHAP Global/Local Explainability Service
│   ├── infrastructure.py # Hardware Health & Resource Monitoring
│   ├── monitoring.py     # Data Drift & Performance Alerting
│   └── main.py           # Core Training Logic
├── artifacts/            # SHAP Waterfall plots and Global Importance
├── pyproject.toml        # Dependency management (uv)
└── README.md             # Project Documentation
```

## Installation & Setup

Ensure you have **uv** installed.

1. **Clone the repository:**
   ```bash
   git clone git@github.com:Axiom-Research-Lab/axiom_mlops_project.git
   cd axiom_mlops_project
   ```

2. **Sync dependencies:**
   ```bash
   uv sync
   ```

## Usage

### 1. Real-Time Inference (FastAPI)
To launch the VodaPay prediction service for live testing:
```bash
uv run uvicorn src.axiom_mlops_project.api:app --reload --reload-dir src
```
**Interactive Documentation:** Once running, access the Swagger UI (`/docs`) to test Instant EFT payloads in real-time.

### 2. Interactive GUI (Gradio)
For a more user-friendly testing experience:
```bash
uv run axiom-interface
```
This launches a web-based dashboard where you can simulate transactions and see immediate results.

### 3. Lineage & Audit Tracking
To execute the data lineage pipeline and generate cloud-hosted audit artifacts:
```bash
uv run python -m axiom_mlops_project.lineage
```

## Model Performance

Current baseline metrics for the Instant EFT Predictor:

